Ionising radiation induces DNA damage mainly via single and double-strand breaks, which can lead to cell death. The linear quadratic (LQ) model is commonly used to describe cell kill from tissue irradiation (Dale 1985), where the cell survival fraction is given as:
1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
\usepackage{amsmath}
\usepackage{wasysym} 
\usepackage{amsfonts} 
\usepackage{amssymb} 
\usepackage{amsbsy}
\usepackage{upgreek}
