where ρc is the clonogenic cell density and V is the tumour volume.

The metastatic control probability (MCP) model (Bernhardt et al
2003, 2004), has been previously used in molecular radiotherapy (Elgqvist et al
2010, Walrand et al
2012). In the context of skeletal metastases, it provides the probability of eradicating all the bone lesions in a given patient and it is defined as the product of the N individual lesion TCPs:
